In [101]:
from collections import Counter
def is_anagram(s1, s2):
  return Counter(s1) == Counter(s2)

s1 = 'listen'
s2 = 'silent'
s3 = 'runner'
s4 = 'neuron'

print('\'listen\' is an anagram of \'silent\' -> {}'.format(is_anagram(s1, s2)))
print('\'runner\' is an anagram of \'neuron\' -> {}'.format(is_anagram(s3, s4)))

'listen' is an anagram of 'silent' -> True
'runner' is an anagram of 'neuron' -> False
In [109]:
def is_palindrome(s):
     reverse = s[::-1]
     if (s == reverse):
        return True
        return False

s1 = 'racecar'
s2 = 'hippopotamus'

print('\'racecar\' a palindrome -> {}'.format(is_palindrome(s1)))
print('\'hippopotamus\' a palindrome -> {}'.format(is_palindrome(s2)))

'racecar' a palindrome -> True
'hippopotamus' a palindrome -> None
